Now the grim war between Trojans and Achaeans\uc0\u8232 was left to run its course. The battle raged,\u8232 this way and that, across the entire plain,\u8232 as warriors hurled bronze-tipped spears at one another,\u8232 between the Simoeis and Xanthus rivers.\
Ajax, son of Telamon, Achaea\'92s tower of strength,\uc0\u8232 was the first to break through ranks of Trojans,\u8232 punching out some breathing room for his companions.\u8232 He hit Acamas, son of Eussorus, a strong brave soldier,\u8232 best of the Thracians. Ajax\'92s spear struck him first [10]\u8232 on the peak of his horse-plumed helmet. The sharp bronze\u8232 drove right into his forehead\'97dead in the centre\'97\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\u8232 straight through bone into the brain. Darkness fell on his eyes.\
