\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0With these words,\uc0\u8232 glorious Hector stretched his hands out for his son.\u8232 The boy immediately shrank back against the breast\u8232 of the finely girdled nurse, crying out in terror\u8232 to see his own dear father, scared at the sight of bronze,\u8232 the horse-hair plume nodding fearfully from his helmet top.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\u8232 The child\'92s loving father laughed, his noble mother, too.\u8232 Glorious Hector pulled the glittering helmet off [580]\u8232 and set it on the ground. Then he kissed his dear son\u8232 and held him in his arms. He prayed aloud to Zeus\u8232 and the rest of the immortals.\
