\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Having said these words,\uc0\u8232 glorious Hector took his plumed helmet in his hands.\u8232 His beloved wife went home, often looking back,\u8232 as she went, crying bitterly. She quickly reached\u8232 the spacious home of Hector, killer of men.\u8232 Inside she met her many servants and bid them all lament. [610]\u8232 So they mourned for Hector in his own house,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\u8232 though he was still alive\'97they thought he\'92d not come back,\u8232 he\'92d not escape the battle fury of Achaean hands.\
